  "department": "Department of Computer Engineering",
  "description": "The Department of Computer Engineering (DCE) was established in 2014 with the objective to furnish students with state-of-the-art quality education and prepare them for a rewarding future. The department focuses on practical and technical skills that students can effectively use in industry and society. It has experienced, dedicated, and foreign-qualified faculty members for its undergraduate and postgraduate programs. The curriculum meets the criteria set by the Higher Education Commission of Pakistan and industrial perspectives, allowing students to explore their interests and capabilities. The department emphasizes Outcome-Based Education (OBE) principles laid down by the Washington Accord and has been accredited by the Pakistan Engineering Council (PEC). It offers advanced computer laboratories and promotes social responsibility through community service and extracurricular activities.",
