    "PhD Computer Engineering": {
      "description": "PhD (Doctor of Philosophy) in Computer Engineering is an esteemed three-year doctorate built around technological advancement and innovation. Following HEC-2021 guidelines and a strong research-oriented learning approach, the program prepares graduates for careers in academia, industry, and research institutions. Students work with experienced faculty across domains such as FPGAs, ASICs, high-performance computing (multicore CPUs, GPUs), and embedded systems, focusing on optimisation for speed, power, energy, reliability, and security. The program requires 24 credit hours of course work plus 30 credit hours of research, and candidates must pass a qualifying exam before commencing doctoral thesis research.",
